Requesterpool@jpdev.pro

Scored byTestilo, procedure tsp24
Digested byTestilo, procedure tdp24

Introduction

This is a digest of results from a battery of accessibility Tests.

The battery includes 1353 automated accessibility tests drawn from ten different packages: Alfa, Axe, Continuum, Equal Access, HTML CodeSniffer, Nu Html Checker, QualWeb, Tenon, Testaro, and WAVE.

These tests were run on the web page named above and gave the page a score of 2324, where 0 would be perfect.

Issue summary

Special issues

log: Score 280. This is based on the amount of browser error logging and miscellaneous logging during the tests.

preventions: Score 150. This is based on tests that the page did not allow to be run. That impedes accessibility progress and risks interfering with tools that users with disabilities need.

solos: Score 28. This is based on issues reported by unclassified tests. Details are in the report.

Classified issues

Issue focusIndication

WCAG: 2.4.7

Score: 215

Issue reports in this category:

  • Package testaro, test focInd, score 165 (Focused element displays no or a nostandard focus indicator)
  • Package alfa, test r65, score 59 (Element in the sequential focus order has no visible focus)
  • Package qualWeb, test QW-ACT-R62, score 60 (Element in the sequential focus order has no visible focus)

Issue linkForcesNewWindow

WCAG: 3.2.5

Score: 179

Issue reports in this category:

  • Package tenon, test 218, score 177 (Link opens in a new window without user control)

Issue textContrastAA

WCAG: 1.4.3

Score: 176

Issue reports in this category:

  • Package alfa, test r69, score 97 (Text outside widget has subminimum contrast)
  • Package axe, test color-contrast, score 52 (Element has insufficient color contrast)
  • Package htmlcs, test e:AAA.1_4_6.G18.Fail, score 8 (Contrast between the text and its background is less than 4.5:1)
  • Package ibm, test IBMA_Color_Contrast_WCAG2AA, score 48 (Contrast ratio of text with background does not meet WCAG 2.1 AA)
  • Package qualWeb, test QW-ACT-R37, score 4 (Text has less than the minimum contrast)
  • Package wave, test c:contrast, score 81 (Very low contrast)

WCAG: 1.3.6

Score: 152

Issue reports in this category:

  • Package alfa, test r57, score 120 (Perceivable text content is not included in any landmark)
  • Package axe, test region, score 21 (Some page content is not contained by landmarks)
  • Package ibm, test Rpt_Aria_OrphanedContent_Native_Host_Sematics, score 54 (Content does not reside within an element with a landmark role)
